Social Distancing

Prevent spreading this virus by maintaing social distance. Read more

Don’t panic

You should concern and take this seriously. But don’t panic. Read more

Keep clean yourself

Wash your hands. With soap. Then wash them again. Read more About Conona Virus

We have to know about the Corona Virus

Coronavirus disease is an infectious disease caused by a newly discovered coronavirus. More than 454,000 people have been infected with a new coronavirus that has spread widely from its origin in China over the past few months. Over 20,500 have already died. Help line: 121-3245-214 0

Total Affected

0

Total Death

0

Total Recovered

* Last updated: April 04, 2020, 05:04 GMT How Coronavirus spread?

How easily virus spreads from person-to-person?

The new coronavirus continues to spread around the world, prompting governments to step up efforts to contain the spread of the disease it causes, offically known as COVID-19.

Person-to-person spread

The virus is thought to spread primarily from person to person. Through the respiratory droplets of people coughing, sneezing or airborne infectious virus. +

From wild animal

Some types of animal pathogenic coronaviruses have been able to infect humans and then spread between humans and restrict contact. +

From many objects

It may be possible that a person can get COVID-19 by touching a surface or object that has the virus on it and then touching their own mouth, nose, eyes. + We have to alart about Corona virus to build extra awareness. Symptoms of Corona infection

There have some Symptoms of Corona

Consultio is a respiratory disease and most infected people will develop mild to moderate symptoms and recover without requiring special treatment.

Fever

The Centers for Disease considers a person to have a fever measured temperature at least 100.4 °F [38 °C]

Read more

Coughing And Sneezing

This means you’ve started coughing repeatedly. As this is viral pneumonia, antibiotics are of no use.

Read more These symptoms may appear 2-14 days after exposure.

Sore throat

Some of the most common causes of Corona virus is throat pain difficulty swallowing.

Read more

Shortness of breath

Shortness of breath and believe you have been exposed to coronavirus.

Read more

Emergency warning:

If you develop emergency warning signs for COVID-19 get medical attention immediately. Emergency warning signs include*:
  • Trouble breathing
  • Persistent pain or pressure in the chest
  • New confusion or inability to arouse
  • Bluish lips or face
What should do or don’t?

We have to maintain some rules to prevent COVID-19

What should do?

Avoid Crowd

Avoid crowded place & keep a space minimum of 2 metres.

Boil Properly

Boil egg and meat properly to kill any germs, boil for about 20 minutes.

Cover cough & sneeze

Cover your mouth and nose with a tissue or your sleeve when you.

Wash your hand

Wash your hands properly and often use 60% alcohol sanitizer.

What shouldn’t do?

Hand Shake

Not shake hands or make close contact with other people.

Touching surface

As virus spreads, common surfaces like lift and doorknobs etc surface.

Don’t touch

Do not touch your eyes, nose or mouth if your hands are not clean.

Avoid contact animals

Wash your hands properly and often use 60% alcohol sanitizer. Prevention of Corona infection

To prevent infection we have to maintain some rules.

COVID-19 is a respiratory disease and most infected people will develop mild to moderate symptoms and recover without requiring special treatment.

Wash your hands

Wash your hands regularly with soap and water, or clean them with alcohol-based hand rub. Read more

Maintain distance

Maintain at least 1 metre distance between you and people coughing or sneezing. Read more

Avoid contact animals

We are providing and dealing with all sorts of legal and professional services. Read more

Wear a facemask

You should wear a facemask when you are around other people if you are sick. Read more

Stay at home

Maintain at least 1 metre distance between you and people coughing or sneezing. Read more

Cover coughs & sneezes

Cover when you cough or sneeze or use the inside of your elbow. Read more More Services Hand cleaning process

Social Distancing

Prevent spreading this virus by maintaing social distance. Read more

Don’t panic

You should concern and take this seriously. But don’t panic. Read more

Keep clean yourself

Wash your hands. With soap. Then wash them again. Read more About Conona Virus

We have to know about the Corona Virus

Coronavirus disease is an infectious disease caused by a newly discovered coronavirus. More than 454,000 people have been infected with a new coronavirus that has spread widely from its origin in China over the past few months. Over 20,500 have already died. Help line: 121-3245-214 0

Total Affected

0

Total Death

0

Total Recovered

* Last updated: April 04, 2020, 05:04 GMT How Coronavirus spread?

How easily virus spreads from person-to-person?

The new coronavirus continues to spread around the world, prompting governments to step up efforts to contain the spread of the disease it causes, offically known as COVID-19.

Person-to-person spread

The virus is thought to spread primarily from person to person. Through the respiratory droplets of people coughing, sneezing or airborne infectious virus. +

From wild animal

Some types of animal pathogenic coronaviruses have been able to infect humans and then spread between humans and restrict contact. +

From many objects

It may be possible that a person can get COVID-19 by touching a surface or object that has the virus on it and then touching their own mouth, nose, eyes. + We have to alart about Corona virus to build extra awareness. Symptoms of Corona infection

There have some Symptoms of Corona

Consultio is a respiratory disease and most infected people will develop mild to moderate symptoms and recover without requiring special treatment.

Fever

The Centers for Disease considers a person to have a fever measured temperature at least 100.4 °F [38 °C]

Read more

Coughing And Sneezing

This means you’ve started coughing repeatedly. As this is viral pneumonia, antibiotics are of no use.

Read more These symptoms may appear 2-14 days after exposure.

Sore throat

Some of the most common causes of Corona virus is throat pain difficulty swallowing.

Read more

Shortness of breath

Shortness of breath and believe you have been exposed to coronavirus.

Read more

Emergency warning:

If you develop emergency warning signs for COVID-19 get medical attention immediately. Emergency warning signs include*:
  • Trouble breathing
  • Persistent pain or pressure in the chest
  • New confusion or inability to arouse
  • Bluish lips or face
What should do or don’t?

We have to maintain some rules to prevent COVID-19

What should do?

Avoid Crowd

Avoid crowded place & keep a space minimum of 2 metres.

Boil Properly

Boil egg and meat properly to kill any germs, boil for about 20 minutes.

Cover cough & sneeze

Cover your mouth and nose with a tissue or your sleeve when you.

Wash your hand

Wash your hands properly and often use 60% alcohol sanitizer.

What shouldn’t do?

Hand Shake

Not shake hands or make close contact with other people.

Touching surface

As virus spreads, common surfaces like lift and doorknobs etc surface.

Don’t touch

Do not touch your eyes, nose or mouth if your hands are not clean.

Avoid contact animals

Wash your hands properly and often use 60% alcohol sanitizer. Prevention of Corona infection

To prevent infection we have to maintain some rules.

COVID-19 is a respiratory disease and most infected people will develop mild to moderate symptoms and recover without requiring special treatment.

Wash your hands

Wash your hands regularly with soap and water, or clean them with alcohol-based hand rub. Read more

Maintain distance

Maintain at least 1 metre distance between you and people coughing or sneezing. Read more

Avoid contact animals

We are providing and dealing with all sorts of legal and professional services. Read more

Wear a facemask

You should wear a facemask when you are around other people if you are sick. Read more

Stay at home

Maintain at least 1 metre distance between you and people coughing or sneezing. Read more

Cover coughs & sneezes

Cover when you cough or sneeze or use the inside of your elbow. Read more More Services Hand cleaning process

How Coronavirus spread?

How easily virus spreads from person-to-person?

The new coronavirus continues to spread around the world, prompting governments to step up efforts to contain the spread of the disease it causes, offically known as COVID-19.

Person-to-person spread

The virus is thought to spread primarily from person to person. Through the respiratory droplets of people coughing, sneezing or airborne infectious virus. +

From wild animal

Some types of animal pathogenic coronaviruses have been able to infect humans and then spread between humans and restrict contact. +

From many objects

It may be possible that a person can get COVID-19 by touching a surface or object that has the virus on it and then touching their own mouth, nose, eyes. + We have to alart about Corona virus to build extra awareness.

Social Distancing

Prevent spreading this virus by maintaing social distance. Read more

Don’t panic

You should concern and take this seriously. But don’t panic. Read more

Keep clean yourself

Wash your hands. With soap. Then wash them again. Read more About Conona Virus

What should do or don’t?

We have to maintain some rules to prevent COVID-19

What should do?

Avoid Crowd

Avoid crowded place & keep a space minimum of 2 metres.

Boil Properly

Boil egg and meat properly to kill any germs, boil for about 20 minutes.

Cover cough & sneeze

Cover your mouth and nose with a tissue or your sleeve when you.

Wash your hand

Wash your hands properly and often use 60% alcohol sanitizer.

What shouldn’t do?

Hand Shake

Not shake hands or make close contact with other people.

Touching surface

As virus spreads, common surfaces like lift and doorknobs etc surface.

Don’t touch

Do not touch your eyes, nose or mouth if your hands are not clean.
